//! # Fusion Monolith Core v3.4.1
//!
//! **The Monolithic Toolchain for Fusion & Rust**
//!
//! This crate combines Check, Build, Security (Audit), Intelligence (LSP), and
//! Execution (Run) into a single shared-memory process.
//!
//! ## Features
//!
//! - **Polyglot Core**: Native support for Fusion language with zero-overhead Rust compatibility
//! - **Flux-Resolve**: GPU-accelerated dependency resolution using CUDA for massive graphs
//! - **Shift-Left Security**: Vulnerability checks during resolution, before download
//! - **Zero-Copy Intelligence**: IDE diagnostics directly from compiler memory
//! - **Self-Optimizing LSP**: Adaptive L1 caching for frequently queried symbols
//! - **Unified TUI**: Single terminal window for all build and runtime information
//!
//! ## Architecture
//!
//! The system is built on four pillars interacting via a central `Arc<RwLock<FusionState>>`:
//!
//! 1. **Orchestrator**: Manages lifecycle state machine
//! 2. **Flux-Resolve**: GPU-accelerated SAT solver for dependency resolution
//! 3. **Auditor**: Real-time security scanning with RustSec integration
//! 4. **Intelligence Server**: Zero-copy LSP with adaptive caching
//!
//! ## Quick Start
//!
//! ```rust,ignore
//! use fusion_monolith_core::prelude::*;
//!
//! fn main() {
//!     let config = MonolithConfig::default();
//!     let monolith = FusionMonolith::new(config);
//!     monolith.run_command(&["fusion", "build"]);
//! }
//! ```

